header.gameNote: BIG WEST MEN'S TOURNAMENT - 1st ROUND AT ANAHEIM CA

article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 84, CS Northridge 76
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. -- Jer'Vaughn Johnson had 20 points and a career-high 12 rebounds to lead Cal State Fullerton to an 84-76 victory over Cal State Northridge in the first round of the Big West Conference tournament Wednesday night. Devon Peltier added 19 points and Gerard Anderson had 15 points, seven assists and six rebounds for the fifth-seeded Titans (16-14), who will face fourth-seeded UC Davis in the quarterfinals Thursday night. Mark Hill scored 15 points for the eighth-seeded Matadors (11-21), who lost eight of their final 10. Willie Galick and Kenny Daniels each added 13 points, and Vincent Cordell had 12 points and a career-best 13 rebounds. Northridge played without forward Lenny Daniel, who was suspended for failing to fulfill academic requirements, the college announced. Daniel was the Matadors' leading rebounder at 7.8 per game and second-leading scorer at 11.7 points. He also set Northridge's single-season record for blocks with 44.
